# Goal Description

The objective is to refactor the entire `orchestrator` and `choreography` layer to strictly adhere to the new architecture pattern. Currently, many functions manually invoke `getFirestore()`, `db.collection()`, or `db.batch()` to read/write from the database. 

The new standard requires using the API Gateway pattern:
1. All client-facing database mutations (Creates, Updates, Deletes) must go through `firestore.run()`.
2. Heavy operations or background processes must use Cloud Tasks to enqueue to `choreography` functions.
3. The orchestrator should only act as a router/trigger, deciding whether to call `firestore.run` directly for synchronous updates, or to enqueue a task to `choreography`.

## User Review Required

> [!WARNING]
> This is a massive refactoring that touches almost every domain module. It involves swapping out native `admin.firestore()` calls with the `firestore.run()` gateway wrapper. Please review the targeted files and confirm if you want to proceed with all of them, or if we should tackle them domain by domain (starting with [claimCanvasSandbox](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/functions/src/orchestrator/canvas.ts#47-98)).

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Global TypeScript Typing & `eslint-disable` Cleanup
We will eliminate all instances of `any` types and `// eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any` across the entire `functions/` directory. Target scopes include:
- [functions/src/types.ts](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/functions/src/types.ts): Remove `any` overrides from `GatewayRequest`.
- [functions/src/gateways/firestore.ts](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/functions/src/gateways/firestore.ts): Eliminate extensive `any` casts in the core DB handler.
- [functions/src/gateways/entityRegistry.ts](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/functions/src/gateways/entityRegistry.ts)
- **All Orchestrator Files**: Review payloads and remove `any` bypasses in [bundle.ts](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/functions/src/orchestrator/bundle.ts), [stand.ts](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/functions/src/choreography/stand.ts), [generic.ts](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/functions/src/orchestrator/generic.ts), etc.
- Also remove `// eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars` where applicable by cleaning up unused exports/imports.

### 2. Immediate Fix: Canvas Orchestrator
#### [MODIFY] [canvas.ts](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/functions/src/orchestrator/canvas.ts)
- Refactor [claimCanvasSandbox](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/functions/src/orchestrator/canvas.ts#47-98) so that instead of using `db.batch().update()`, it uses `firestore.run()` with `actionId: "update"` to assign the `orgId` and `ownId`.

### 3. Choreography Services
#### [MODIFY] [canvas.ts](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/functions/src/choreography/canvas.ts)
- Refactor [handleCanvasDeleteNode](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/functions/src/choreography/canvas.ts#300-323) to use `firestore.run()` with `actionId: "hard_delete"` or `"soft_delete"` instead of `nodeRef.delete()`.
#### [MODIFY] [auth.ts](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/functions/src/choreography/auth.ts)
- Replace direct `db.collection("auths")` usage with `firestore.run`.
#### [MODIFY] [correlator.ts](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/functions/src/choreography/correlator.ts)
- Replace all direct `db.collection()` inserts/updates for log correlation with `firestore.run`.

### 4. Orchestrator Services (Domain by Domain)
